- Use only "EE" rated power industrial vehicles or manual power jacks to transport aerosol pallet loads within the facility;
- In production areas only store the aerosol products required for one-shift;
- Aerosol products can only be stored in yellow aerosol storage cages and in designated areas for "holding" and are prohibited from being stored near aisle intersections or in heavy traffic areas;
- At critical points on conveyors, such as bends in lines where carton jams are likely to occur, additional protection such as a wire mesh barrier on the sides, a net placed below the belts, video monitoring, etc. are required to be installed;
- Damaged cartons containing aerosol products, or individual cans, must be removed immediately from the storage or operating areas and stored in metal 55-gallon Hazardous Waste drums in the "Return Goods" Satellite Accumulation Area; and
- Associates who may handle aerosol products must be trained on the hazards associated with the product(s), the importance of identifying damaged containers, how to handle damaged containers, and how to identify "EE" rated equipment.

Additional precautionary measures to be taken, but that are not included in M0002 include:

- Flammable or combustible liquids will not be stored within 2.4 m (8 ft) of aerosols;
- Do not locate high hazard operations (i.e., battery charging) within 8 m (25 ft) of the Warehouse Aerosol Room.

